📸 Recap what i studies at Yonsei

Here are the courses I enrolled last semester and this semester 

- Introduction to computational linguist 
- Error analysis of second language learners (study about how to analyze learner courpus) 
- Theories of lexicography (how to make good dictionary) 
- Seminar in Korean language education 
- Teaching method of Korean pronunciation 
- Teaching method of Korean speaking and writing 
The professors at Yonsei University are very famous and recognized experts in their respective fields. A lot of courses surprised me because they offered in-depth insights and unique perspectives that I had not encountered before.

I’m so glad I chose to study abroad at Yonsei.
And I definitely believe it was one of the best decisions I’ve made for my education and personal growth.

I never thought coming to Korea 
would change my life this much 🇰🇷💫

I’ve never considered myself
 to be especially pretty
just an ordinary face in the crowd.

But I’ve always tried to 
live my life the best I could.
As a bookworm who got the
 chance to study here 
through a scholarship, 
I discovered something surprising…

The truth is I’m not “not beautiful.”
I just didn’t know how to take care of myself.
But after doing my own research, 
I realized that self-improvement
doesn’t have to be hard or painful
 as I used to think.

One thing that always bothered me 
was my double chin.
But I didn’t want surgery

Then I found something 
in Korea called LAMS 
a treatment that removes fat
 without surgery.

It’s so simple!
Exercise might take months and 
the results still might not be noticeable…
But after just one hour of LAMS, 
my double chin disappeared! 😭
And the next day, 
I was back to my daily routine
 like nothing happened.

Sometimes… 
all it takes is the courage to 
start learning how to care for yourself.
That alone can change your life 💖

🌟 Global Korea Scholarship: Universities for Business Majors (Type B) 🌟
Are you dreaming of studying business in Korea under the prestigious Global Korea Scholarship (GKS)? Let’s explore some incredible Type B universities offering top-notch business and MBA programs tailored to your aspirations! 🎓✨

🔹 Busan University of Foreign Studies (BUFS) 💼 Why BUFS?
* Offers a highly-regarded MBA program through the Graduate School of Management (GSM).
* MBA program  designed for professionals with business experience.
* Strong focus on global and practical business education.

🔹 Pusan National University (PNU) 🌍 Specialties: International Business & Marketing
* Comprehensive coursework to build leadership and global business acumen.

🔹 Changwon National University 📚 Established Excellence
* MBA program available since 1989!
* Integrates theoretical knowledge with practical corporate strategies.

🔹 Chonnam National University 🚀 Strategic Focus
* Offers a robust MBA program emphasizing business administration and innovative management strategies.

🔹 Hannam University 🔧 Practical Learning
* Focuses on developing skills for effective management in diverse business settings.

🔹 Kyungpook National University 🏅 Leadership Training
* Combines research-driven insights with practical business applications.
